race.comment: Looks another good race for TOUCHDOWN (3) who was a dominant winner here over 1600m last time out, setting midfield off a strong tempo and powering away to score by 3.5 lengths in good overall time. He'll have no issue rising to 1800m and should even improve going to it with natural upside. Looks better than midweek grade and should be winning. ALBANIAN I AM (6) brings completely different form having tried hard in the Donald Cup last time out. He struggles to win but is going quite well and could surprise. FIORENOT (4) and SCINTILLANTE (2) come through the race behind TOUCHDOWN. Both should appreciate the rise in trip, but both are likely to settle behind the favourite again and it's hard to see them turning the tables from there.
